<head>
   <title>

11th Annual IEEE Conference on Computational Complexity (CCC '96)


</title>
</head>
<body text="#000000" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="../sand.gif">

<FORM ACTION=https://secure.computer.org/cgi-bin/cspress/shopcart.bat METHOD=POST>

<INPUT TYPE=Hidden NAME=catnumber VALUE="pr07386">

<blockquote>
<h2><br>

11th Annual IEEE Conference on Computational Complexity
(CCC '96) 
<br><font size=+0><i>(formerly: Structure in Complexity Theory Conference)</I></font>


</h2>
<h3>

May 24-27, 1996 &#151; Philadelphia, PA 

</h3>

<p><b>Partial List of Papers:</b> An Isomorphism for Circuit Complexity
• Parallel Complexity Hierarchies Based on PRAMs and DLOGTIME-Uniform Circuits
• Collapsing Oracle-Tape Hierarchies • On Coherence, Random-Self-Reducibility,
and Self-Correction • Error Reduction by Parallel Repetition • VC Dimension
in Circuits Complexity • Logspace Printability and Isomorphism • A Comparison
of Weak Completeness Notions • Stochastic Properties of Lutz-Random Sequences
• The Complexity of Knowledge Representation • Zero Knowledge and the Chromatic
Number • DNA Models and Algorithms for NP-Complete Problems • Reversible
Simulation of Irreversible Computation</p>

<p><b><a href="../../conferen/proceed/ccc96/toc.htm" target=_top>Abstracts</a></b></p>


<p><i>320 pages. May 1996. Softcover. ISBN 0-8186-7386-9. 
<br>Catalog # PR07386 &#151; $40.00 Members / $80.00 List</i></p>

</blockquote>

