<h2><br>

1995 International Test Conference (ITC '95)
<br><i><font SIZE=+1>Driving Down the Cost of Test</font></i>

</h2>
<h3>

October 21-25, 1995 &#151; Washington, DC

</h3>

<p><b>Contents: </b>New Test Consideration for Mixed-Signal Devices • Quality,
IDDQ, and the DUT Interface • Delay Testing • Microprocessor Test • MCM
Test Methods • Generation and Fault Simulation • Design for Testability
• New Test Techniques for Mixed-Signal Devices • Applications of Test Cost
Analysis • High-Speed ATE Architectures and Timing • Defect Detection and
Diagnosis • Performance-Driven BIST Insertion • IC-Defect-Detection: Advancements
in Design, Test, and Analysis Methods • IC Testing and Diagnosis • Topics
in Test Techniques • Successful Experiences with MCM Test • Synthesis for
Testability • Software Testing • Test Synthesis • Systems and Testing:
Practical Applications and Costs • BIST Pattern Generation and Compaction
• Design and Simulation Topics • Changing the Test Paradigm: ATE and Board
Test Systems</p>

<p><i>800 pages. Hardcover. October 1995. ISBN 0-7803-2992-9. 
<br>Catalog # RS00033 &#151; $75.00 Members / $150.00 List</i></p>

