<blockquote>
<h2><br>

1996 International Conference on Robotics and Automation
<br><I>(4-Volume Set)</I>

</h2>
<h3>

April 22-28, 1996  &#151; Minneapolis, MN

</h3>

<P><B>Contents: </B>Tactile Sensor Technologies  •  Techniques for Robot Programming  •  Space Robots  •  Vision-Guided Navigation  •  Motion and Path Planning  •  Redundant Robots  •  Petri Nets  •  Acutators  •  Biped Locomotion  •  Adaptive Robot Control  •  Force Control  •  Dynamic Identification  •  Sonar Sensing Techniques  •  Friction-Compensation Control  •  Fixture Design  •  Flexible Manufacturing Systems  •  Haptic Interface  •  Discrete Event and Industrial Control  •  Force Control and Manipulation  •   Calibration  •  Multi-Sensor Fusion  •  Control Architectures  •  Environmental Modeling  •  Collision Detection  •  Surgical Robots  •  Mine and Field Applications  •  Human-Robot Coordination  •  Mechanisms  •  Application-Driven Teleoperation  •  Collision Avoidance  •  Discrete Event Dynamic Systems  •  Bio-Robotic Systems  •  Hazardous Industrial Applications  •  Robotic Vision  •  Contact  •  Teleoperation  •  Cooperative Mobile Robots  •  Grasping Mechanisms  •  Assembly  •  Optimal Robot Control  •  Neural Networks Applications  •  Multirobot Systems  •  Model Generation and CAD  •  Impact Control  •   Neural Net Control  •  Flexible Robot Modeling and Simulation  •    Active Vision  •  Grasp Synthesis  •  Underwater Robotics  •  Fuzzy Control Applications  •  Real-Time Vision  •   Virtual Reality and Collaboration  •  Mobile Manipulation and Planning  •  Task Planning and Scheduling  •  Micro/Macro Robotics  •  Vision-Based Control  •  Human Skill Acquisition  •  Control of Walking Robots  •  Mobile Robot Control    •  Visual Tracking  •  Human Robot Skill  •  Autonomous Vehicles  •  Kinematics  •  Inspection  Object Recognition  •  Tactile Sensing  •  Mobile Robot Applications  •  Navigation and Control  •    Parallel Manipulators</P>

<P><I>3,770 pages. May 1996. Softcover. ISBN 0-7803-2988-0. 
<BR>Catalog # RS00096 &#151; $165.00 Members / $330.00 List</I></P>


