<table border=2 cellpadding=7>
<caption><b>Table 1.</b><i> Relationship of the service-profit chain to EDA issues.</i>
</caption>

<th><tr><td><b>Element of service-profit 
<br>chain, specific EDA problems</b></td><td><b>How EDA companies could 
<br>alleviate problems</b></td><td><b><br>Results of correcting problems </b></td><td><b>Potential benefits to EDA 
<br>companies</b></td></tr></th>

<tr>
<td valign=top><font size=1>Customer satisfaction
<ul>
<li>Design cost growing; must use internal resources heavily
<li>EDA not keeping up with design complexity</font>
</ul></font></td>

<td valign=top><font size=1>Focusing their products and services on helping individual customers succeed</font></td>

<td valign=top><font size=1>Improved customer loyalty; loyal customers will
<ul><li>Repeat and make new purchases based on value, rather than remain locked into solutions to avoid costs of switching
<li>Refer products to peers
<li>Demonstrate willingness to adopt mutually beneficial pricing models</ul></font></td>

<td valign=top><font size=1>Increased revenue
<br>
<br>Higher potential profitability based on value pricing
<br>
<br>Can direct capital in the right direction in, for example, research and development</td></font></tr>

<tr><td valign=top><font size=1>Employee satisfaction, productivity, loyalty
<ul>
<li>High personnel turnover
<li>Loss in key knowledge
</ul></font></td>

<td valign=top><font size=1>Providing a work environment that values customer service as highly as technological innovation</font></td>

<td valign=top><font size=1>Retention of key employees
<br>
<br>Ability to attract new talent</font></td>

<td valign=top><font size=1>Prevents loss of key employees and lessens need to compete for small pool of new talent
<br>
<br>Prevents such employees from starting competitive businesses</td></tr></font>
