<h2>About the Authors</h2>
<p><b>Nayeem Islam</b> is a research staff member at IBM's TJ Watson's research center. He is leading a project on the design and implementation of an adaptable object-oriented operating system. Parts of the operating system will be shipped as part of IBM's product line.

He was one of the principle designers and implementers of Choices, an operating system built using object-oriented frameworks. This work has influenced many other research projects, such as the Spring Operating system from Sun Microsystems and as well as commercial projects at companies such as IBM and Microsoft. In particular, the technology has been used to build the IBM OS/400 operating system and the Microsoft OLE foundation classes. Prior to his work on operating systems, he was a project leader at Sun Microsystems Inc. where he led the design and implementation of an object-oriented graphical user interface tool kit. He made major contributions to the design and implementation of the Xt Intrinsics tool kit version four. The code and documentation for this product are used worldwide. </p>

