<HEAD>
<TITLE> Background</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><P>
 <HR> <A NAME=tex2html57 HREF=subsection3_2_1.html><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html55 HREF=hainesm.html><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html49 HREF=section3_1.html><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/previous_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html58 HREF=subsection3_2_1.html> Lightweight Thread Libraries</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html56 HREF=hainesm.html>On the Design of </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html50 HREF=section3_1.html> Introduction</A>
<HR> <P>
<H1><A NAME=SECTION0002000000000000000> Background</A></H1>
<P>
<A NAME=secback><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/invis_anchor.xbm"></A>
<P>
Chant provides an interface for talking threads by 
merging the interfaces of a communication system and a
lightweight thread system.
Thus, our design is concerned with two interfaces: the <em>user interface</em>
and the <em>system interface</em>.
The user interface is the one which provides the portable talking threads,
and would be the target interface for parallelizing compilers or 
explicit parallel programming.
The system interface defines the underlying systems upon which 
Chant relies, and is divided into two portions: 
a thread library interface and a communication library interface.
Thus, the portability of Chant is defined by the system interface
and the underlying packages that can accommodate that interface.
By basing the system interface on existing standards for lightweight
threads and interprocessor communication,
Chant is positioned to be highly portable across many 
distributed platforms,
including multicomputers and workstation clusters.
We now examine the system level interface for lightweight thread
and communication libraries.
<P>
<HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html59 HREF=subsection3_2_1.html#SECTION0002100000000000000> Lightweight Thread Libraries</A>
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html60 HREF=subsection3_2_2.html#SECTION0002200000000000000> Communication Libraries</A>
</UL>
<HR>

</BODY>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>haines@icase.edu <BR>
Mon Aug  1 14:13:52 EDT 1994</I>
</ADDRESS>
