<HEAD>
<TITLE> Experimental Results</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY><P>
 <HR> <A NAME=tex2html139 HREF=subsection3_4_1.html><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html137 HREF=hainesm.html><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME=tex2html131 HREF=subsection3_3_4.html><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/previous_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html140 HREF=subsection3_4_1.html> Point-to-Point Communication Overheads</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html138 HREF=hainesm.html>On the Design of </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html132 HREF=subsection3_3_4.html> Remote Thread Operations</A>
<HR> <P>
<H1><A NAME=SECTION0004000000000000000> Experimental Results</A></H1>
<P>
<A NAME=secexp><IMG ALIGN=MIDDLE SRC="http://www.icase.edu/~haines/images/invis_anchor.xbm"></A>
<P>
It is not our goal to argue that threads themselves are useful
for programming distributed memory multiprocessors.
Instead, our goal is to demonstrate that our design decisions
were effective in implementing a talking threads interface, 
namely Chant.
The Chant layers are currently implemented and executing on a 
network of Sun workstations (using p4 <A HREF=bibliography3_8.html#p4>[5]</A> and pthreads <A HREF=bibliography3_8.html#Muel93>[19]</A>),
and on the Intel Paragon (using NX and a small, hand-coded thread library).
To demonstrate the effectiveness of our design decisions for the 
point-to-point communication layer, we perform two sets of experiments
on the Intel Paragon.
The first experiment is designed to measure the relative overhead of 
thread-to-thread communication using Chant primitives (layered atop NX)
with process-to-process communication using NX primitives.
The second experiment is designed to test the various scheduling techniques
that are available when polling for outstanding messages in point-to-point
communication.
<P>
<HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html141 HREF=subsection3_4_1.html#SECTION0004100000000000000> Point-to-Point Communication Overheads</A>
<LI> <A NAME=tex2html142 HREF=subsection3_4_2.html#SECTION0004200000000000000> Message Polling</A>
</UL>
<HR>

</BODY>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>haines@icase.edu <BR>
Mon Aug  1 14:13:52 EDT 1994</I>
