<!-- Row # 4 -->
<Tr><Td align=center><Center>C</CENTER></Td><Td align=center><Center>1720 Hz</CENTER></Td><Td align=center><Center>1800 Hz</CENTER></Td><Td align=center><Center>1880 Hz</CENTER></Td><Td align=center><Center>1960 Hz</CENTER></Td></Tr>

</Table>

<P><B>V.21: 300 Bit/s Duplex Modem Standardized for Use in the General Switched Telephone Network</B></P>

<P>The V.21 recommendation is used on slow-speed systems. Some vendors offer speeds of 50-300 bits/s. V.21 is offered by some vendors as a small inexpensive modem that fits under a standard telephone, but it is old and seldom used.</P>

<P>This recommendation uses frequency shift modulation with the modulation rate equal to the bit rate. The mean frequency for channel 1 is 1080 Hz; for channel 2 it is 1750 Hz. Both synchronous or asynchronous procedures are allowed. The nominal characteristic frequencies are shown below. Each channel uses one of two frequencies to represent binary data:</P>

<Table Width=50% Align=Center Colspec="L20 L20 ">

<!-- Row # 1 -->
<Tr><Th align=left><b>Channel 1</Th><Th align=left>Channel 2</B></Th></Tr>

<!-- Row # 2 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>F<sub>A</sub> = 1180 Hz (0) </Td><Td align=left>F<sub>A</sub> = 1850 Hz (0) </Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 3 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>F<sub>Z</sub> =  980 Hz (1) </Td><Td align=left>F<sub>Z</sub> = 1650 Hz (1)</Td></Tr>
</Table>
V.21 uses the V.24 circuits as described in Table 5-3.</P>

<Table Border=1 Align=Center Colspec="L20 L20 L20 L20 L20 ">
<Caption Align=Top><b>TABLE 5-3.  V.21 Interchange Circuits </b></Caption>

<!-- Row # 1 -->
<Tr><Th align=Center COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=CENTER><B><Center>Interchange circuit </B></CENTER></Th>
<TH align=Center VALIGN=BOTTOM ROWSPAN=2><B><Center>General switched telephone network including terminals equipped for manual calling, manual answering, automatic calling, automatic answering<small><SUP>1</SUP></small></B></CENTER></TH>
<TH align=Center COLSPAN=2 VALIGN=BOTTOM><B><Center>Nonswitched leased telephone circuit<small><SUP>1</SUP></small></B></CENTER></TH>
</Tr>

<!-- Row # 4 -->
<Tr><Td align=CENTER WIDTH=100><B>No.</B></Td><Td WIDTH=100 align=CENTER><B>Designation</B></Td></Td><Td align=CENTER WIDTH=100><B>Point - to - point</B></Td><Td align=CENTER WIDTH=100><B>Multi-point</B></Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 5 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>102</Td><Td align=left>Signal Ground or Common Return</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 6 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>103</Td><Td align=left>Transmitted Data</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 7 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>104</Td><Td align=left>Received Data</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 8 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>105</Td><Td align=left>Request to Send</Td><Td align=CENTER>&#151</Td><Td align=CENTER>x<SUP>2</SUP></Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 9 -->
<Tr><Td align=left>106</Td><Td align=left>Ready for Sending</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td><Td align=CENTER>x</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 10 -->
