<FONT SIZE="2"><small><SUP>1</SUP></small>All essential interchange circuits and any others that are provided shall comply with the requirements of recommendation V.24. All interchange circuits indicated by X shall be properly terminated in the data equipment and in the data circuit-terminating equipment in accordance with the appropriate recommendation.<br>
<SUP>2</SUP>These circuits are required when the clock is in the modem.</FONT>

<P><B>V.26: 2400 Bit/s Modem Standardized for Use on Four-Wire Leased Telephone-Type Lines</B>
<P>The V.26 recommendation is not used very much today.  Some vendors now offer V.26bis or V.26ter.
<P>This type of modem uses four-phase modulation with a synchronous mode of operation and may also include a backward channel of up to 75 baud.
<P>The recommendation operates with a carrier frequency at 1800 Hz and with a modulation rate of 1200 baud.  Data are encoded into pairs of bits (dibits); each dibit is encoded as a phase change relative to the immediately preceding signal. Two alternatives exist as to how the coding is performed. These alternatives are shown in Table 5-10. The V.24 circuits are used as described in Table 5-11.</P>

<P>
<Table Border=1 Width=80% Align=Center Colspec="L20 L20 L20 ">
<Caption Align=Top><b>TABLE 5-10.  V.26 Encoding</b></Caption>

<!-- Row # 2 -->
<Tr><td>&nbsp;</td><Td align=center colspan=2><B>Phase Change<small><SUP>1</SUP></small></B></Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 3 -->
<Tr><Td align=center><B>Dibit</B></Td><Td align=center><B> Alternative A</B></Td><Td align=center><B>Alternative B</B></Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 4 -->
<Tr><Td align=center>00</Td><Td align=center>0&#176</Td><Td align=center>+ 45&#176</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 5 -->
<Tr><Td align=center>01</Td><Td align=center>+ 90&#176</Td><Td align=center>+ 135&#176</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 6 -->
<Tr><Td align=center>11</Td><Td align=center>+ 180&#176</Td><Td align=center>+ 225&#176</Td></Tr>

<!-- Row # 7 -->
<Tr><Td align=center>10</Td><Td align=center>+ 270&#176</Td><Td align=center>+ 315&#176</Td></Tr>

</Table>
<FONT SIZE="2"><small><SUP>1</SUP></small>The phase change is the phase shift in the transition region from the center of one signaling element to the center <br>of the following signaling element.</FONT></P>

<P>
<Table Border=1 Width=80% Align=Center Colspec="L20 L20 L20 L20 ">
