</Table>
<FONT SIZE="2"><small><SUP>1</SUP></small>All essential interchange circuits and any others that are provided shall comply with requirements of recommendation V.24. All interchange circuits indicated by X shall be properly terminated in the data equipment and in the data circuit-terminating equipment in accordance with the appropriate recommendation.<br>
<small><SUP>2</SUP></small>This circuit shall be capable of operation as circuit 108/1 or circuit 108/2.</FONT></P>

<P><B>V.26ter: 2400 Bit/s Duplex Modem Using the Echo Cancellation Technique Standardized for Use on the General Switched Telephone Network and on Point-to-Point, Two-Wire Leased Telephone-Type Circuits</B>
<P>V.26ter has not seen extensive use. The principal characteristics of this modem are as follows:
<OL>
<LI>FDX mode of operation is possible on switched and point-to-point leased circuits.
<LI>HDX mode of operation is possible on switched and point-to-point leased circuits.
<LI>Channel separation is done by echo cancellation.
<LI>Differential phase-shift modulation is performed for each channel with synchronous line transmission at 1200 baud.
<LI>A scrambler is included.
<LI>An equalizer is included.
<LI>Test facilities are included.
<LI>Operation with DTE is available in the following modes: 2400 bit/s synchronous, 1200 bit/s synchronous (fall-back rate), 2400 bit/s start/stop (optional), and 1200 bit/s start/stop (optional) (fall-back rate).
<LI>An included operating sequence is intended to allow interworking with two-wire FDX 4800 bit/s modem.
</OL>

<P>The carrier frequency operates at 1800 Hz. Power levels conform to V.2, and the signaling rate is 1200 baud with the 2400 and 1200 bit/s rate coded as shown in Tables 5-13 and 5-14.</P>

<Table Border=1 Width=80% Align=Center Colspec="L20 L20 ">
