<P>Synchronization signals are provided by two segments. The first segment is comprised of continuous phase reversals for 32 symbol intervals. The second segment is derived by scrambling the data stream and by using phase changes (see Table 5-15). The V.24 circuits are used as described in Table 5-16.</P>

