<FONT SIZE="2"><small><SUP>1</SUP></small>Circuits conform to V.28. The other circuits are a balanced pair.</FONT></P>

<P>While widely used, the V.35 specification is an awkward interface, with its combinations of balanced and unbalanced operations. The ITU-T is encouraging the migration to other recommendations, such as V.36, but V.35 will remain in the industry for many years because of its installed base.
<P>EIA-530-A can interwork with a V.35 interface. Since some of the V.35 interchange circuits are unbalanced, and the EIA-530-A interchange circuits are balanced, conversion must take place between the interfaces for interchange circuits CA (request to send), CB (clear to send), and CF (received line signal detector). Table 5-31 shows the relationships of the interchange circuits between EIA-530-A and V.35.</P>

