<small><SUP>2</SUP></small> Equipment may be in service that does not implement these circuits.<br>
<small><SUP>3</SUP></small> Interchange circuits 102a and 102b are required where the electrical characteristics defined in recommendation V.10 are used.</FONT></P>


<P><B>V.37 Synchronous Data Transmission at a Data Signaling Rate Higher than 72 Kbits/s Using
60-108 kHz Group Band Circuits</B>
<P>This modem is also used on leased circuits. The only group reference pilot frequency which can be used in conjunction with this modem is 104.08 kHz. Its principal characteristics are as follows:
<OL>
<LI>It provides transmission of any type of high-speed synchronous data in FDX constant carrier mode on four-wire (60-108 kHz) group band circuits.
<LI>It provides primary data signaling rates of up to 144 kbits/s.
<LI>An automatic adaptive equalizer is included.
<LI>It provides partial response pulse amplitude single sideband signaling and modulation.
<LI>An overhead-free multiplexer combining existing data signaling rates can be included.
<LI>Optional voice channel can be included.
</OL>
<P>V. 37 uses the V. 24 circuits as described in Table 5-33.</P>

<P></P>
