<FONT SIZE="2"><small><SUP>1</SUP></small> When the modem is installed at the repeater station, this interface should appear at the customer's premises without restrictions regarding the data signaling rate and the provision of the voice channel. The method to achieve this is subject to national regulations. <br>
<small><SUP>2</SUP></small> The provision of this conductor is optional.<br>
<small><SUP>3</SUP></small> Interchange circuits 102a and 102b are required where the electrical characteristics defined in recommendation V.10 are used. <br>
<small><SUP>4</SUP></small> Not essential in subchannel. <br>
<small><SUP>5</SUP></small> During the synchronization process of the main modem, the OFF condition of circuit 106 is signaled at all port interfaces. <br>
<small><SUP>6</SUP></small> Circuit 142 is present on all ports of the multiplexer, but may be activated on an individual port basis for individual port tests. All are activated simultaneously for entire modem tests.</FONT></P>

<hr>

