<h2>About the Author</h2>
<p><b>Homer R. Oldfield</b> received his BS and MS from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in Aeronautical Engineering.  He served in the U.S. Army for 4 years during World War II.  From 1945 to 1958, he held various positions with General Electric, including General Manager and Founder of the GE Computer Department, primarily based around the construction of the Bank of America ERMA system.  He later served as Group Vice President for Raytheon Co., President of Searle Medidata, Inc. and President of Medequip Corporation.  He now works as an industry consultant and writer.</p>

