<h2>About the Authors</h2>
<p><b>David A. Wheeler</b>  is a research staff member at the Institute for Defense Analyses (IDA), a federally funded research and development center located in Alexandria, Virginia. His research interests are in development techniques for large and high-risk software systems, including software risk assessment, inspections, CASE tools, notations and methodologies, object-oriented approaches, C++, and Ada. <b>Bill Brykczynski</b>  is also a research staff member at IDA. His research interests are software defect prevention, software inspection, software testing, risk analysis, and software process improvement. <b>Reginald N. Meeson, Jr., </b> is also a research staff member at IDA. His interests include programming language design (in particular, abstraction mechanisms and type systems) and how people use language features as tools to solve complex problems.</p>

